HEADWORD: Mummer
<hw>Mumm"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>mommeur</ets>. See <er>Mumm</er>, and cf. <er>Momier</er>.]</ety>
<def>One who mumms, or makes diversion in disguise; a masker; a
buffon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Jugglers and dancers, antics, <qex>mummers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mummery</ent>⟦br⟧
